==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Receivers certificate
<hw>Re*ceiv"er's cer*tif"i*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>An
acknowledgment of indebtedness made by a receiver under order of court
to obtain funds for the preservation of the assets held by him, as for
operating a railroad. Receivers' certificates are ordinarily a first
lien on the assets, prior to that of bonds or other
securities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Receivership</ent>⟦br⟧
